{
  "id": 6192419898654720,
  "name": "Deprecate special font size rules for H1 within some elements",
  "summary": "The HTML spec contains a list of [special rules for H1 tags](https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/rendering.html#sections-and-headings) nested within `article`, `aside`, `nav`, or `section` tags. Chrome 140 deprecates these special rules, because they can cause accessibility issues. For example, they can visually reduce the font size for nested `h1` tags so that they look like `h2` tags, but nothing in the accessibility tree reflects this demotion.",
  "markdown_fields": [
    "summary"
